OL,4,CWarning to buyers of used vehicles
OL,6,FThe Ombudsman pointed to an engineer's
OL,7,Freport carried out after the accident,
OL,8,Fsuggesting the wheel and drive shaft
OL,9,Fhad been "improperly torqued".
OL,11,FThat report said this would be
OL,12,F"impossible to prove" due to the car
OL,13,Fbeing driven "in a distressed
OL,14,Fcondition".
OL,16,FBut the Ombudsman concluded the car
OL,17,Fwas "not of satisfactory quality" when
OL,18,Fsupplied.
